    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-09-18T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-09-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="70"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d70">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">662A.00/9–1854</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Chancellor <persName corresp="#p_ADENAUERK1" type="to">Adenauer</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d70fn1">This message was transmitted to Bonn in priority
                        telegram 772 of Sept. 18 with instructions that <persName
                            corresp="#p_CONANTJB1">Conant</persName> personally deliver it to
                            <persName corresp="#p_ADENAUERK1">Adenauer</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-09-18">September 18,
                            1954</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I much appreciated the opportunity of talking to you and the chance to secure
                    your views in detail on Thursday and Friday. I am sure this exchange will prove
                    of great value for purposes of our common objectives in forthcoming
                    international meetings. In frank discussions with <persName corresp="#p_EDENSA1"
                        >Eden</persName> yesterday I was struck by his evident desire to find <pb
                        facs="0159" n="1227" xml:id="pg_1227"/> mutually satisfactory solution in
                    near future in spite of difficulties that can be foreseen. I stressed to him
                    importance of careful preparation, which I feel is not yet adequate, in advance
                    of nine-power meeting to insure basis for positive accomplishment consistent
                    with continued progress toward genuine European unity which can alone command
                    unreserved support of your Government and mine. <persName corresp="#p_EDENSA1"
                        >Eden</persName> is hopeful that <persName corresp="#p_MENDESFP1"
                        >Mendes-France</persName> will concur in <gloss target="#t_NATO1"
                        >NATO</gloss>–Brussels Pact solution acceptable to other governments
                    consulted, but awaits more specific information promised by <persName
                        corresp="#p_MENDESFP1">Mendes-France</persName> in next few days, which I
                    understand will also be communicated to all the other interested
                    governments.</p>
                <p>With kindest regards,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DULLESJF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Foster Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
